    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review theory test questions on HGV hazards",
        "additional_details": "This could include:\r\nVideos into the hazard perception part of the test.\r\nQuestions about the hazards of HGV\u2019s including blind spots, turning circles.\r\n \r\nStatistics consistently show that the vast majority of all road accidents, including those involving cars and HGVs, are attributed to human factors and are therefore preventable.\r\nGeneral road safety studies suggest that approximately 97% of all road accidents are preventable. Safety experts emphasise that managing road risk and improving driver behaviour through training can significantly reduce incident rates.\r\n",
        "background": "Review the frequency of questions that are asked on HGV hazards in the DVSA driving theory test to ensure learners are sufficiently prepared.",
